    "body": "### Problem\n\nThis may not be a bug. Looking at the documentation it says\r\n> With relative=editor (row=0,col=0) refers to the top-left corner of the screen-grid\r\n\r\nIf this refers to a \"point\" and not a \"cell\", then it is behaving correctly and there is no bug.\r\n\r\nThe closest vim has to this is `popup_create`'s `pos` option. There it is a cell.\r\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nSource the following script. The floating window is in the box. Enter the normal\r\nmode mapping `Z1` to re-draw the floating using the next anchor.\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\nvim.o.scl = \"yes\"\r\n\r\n--               _______\r\n--              |X      | \r\n--              |       | \r\n--               -------\r\n\r\n-- Z1 - Delete current floater, new floater at next window anchor\r\n\r\nlocal pos_map = {\r\n    \"NW\",\r\n    \"NE\",\r\n    \"SW\",\r\n    \"SE\",\r\n}\r\nlocal pos_index = 0\r\n\r\nlocal popup_wid\r\nlocal function Pop1()\r\n    local bnr = vim.api.nvim_create_buf(false, true)\r\n    assert(bnr, \"Failed to create buffer\")\r\n    vim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(bnr, 0, -1, true, {'simple', 'win'})\r\n\r\n    vim.api.nvim_set_option_value(\"bufhidden\", \"wipe\", {buf = bnr})\r\n    vim.api.nvim_set_option_value(\"modifiable\", true, {buf = bnr})\r\n    local opts = {\r\n        row = 5,\r\n        col = 19,\r\n        relative = \"editor\",\r\n        style = \"minimal\",\r\n        width = 7,\r\n        height = 2,\r\n        focusable = false,\r\n    }\r\n    opts.anchor = pos_map[pos_index + 1]\r\n    pos_index = (pos_index + 1) % #pos_map\r\n    popup_wid = vim.api.nvim_open_win(bnr, false, opts)\r\n    vim.print(string.format(\"WindowCreate: %s\", opts.anchor))\r\nend\r\n\r\nPop1()\r\n\r\nlocal function next_anchor()\r\n    vim.api.nvim_win_close(popup_wid, true)\r\n    Pop1()\r\nend\r\n\r\nvim.keymap.set('n', 'Z1', next_anchor)\r\n\r\nvim.o.tm = 5000\r\n```\r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nExpected the \"X\" to be covered by each anchor corner. (but that may be based on a flawed understanding).\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/20251be15a4ad3f6e7016450ca3338d52b2f0951\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno but not entirely applicable\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nubuntu\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\ngnome\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nmake install",
